==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impinge
<hw>Im*pinge"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Impinged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Impinging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>impingere</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>pangere</ets> to
fix, strike; prob. akin to <ets>pacisci</ets> to agree, contract. See
<er>Pact</er>, and cf. <er>Impact</er>.]</ety> <def>To fall or dash
against; to touch upon; to strike; to hit; to clash with; -- with on or
<xex>upon</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cause of reflection is not the <qex>impinging</qex> of light
on the solid or impervious parts of bodies.</q> <rj><qau>Sir I.
Newton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But, in the present order of things, not to be employed without
<qex>impinging</qex> on God's justice.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Warburton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impingement</ent>⟦br⟧
